other_tests.findings: The liver is normal without focal or echotextural abnormality. The main portal vein is patent with hepatopetal flow. The gallbladder is normal without wall thickening or gallstone. The common duct measures 4 mm and there is no intra- or extra-hepatic bile duct dilatation. The pancreatic duct measures 2 mm. The pancreas is otherwise unremarkable.
